76561198003030375,Recommended,304910,14025397,"Posted: 16 January, 2015",all,The_Cpt_FROGGY,"Sky Gamblers: Storm Raiders~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~First of all, I must say that I am not a fan of flight simulation at all. And there is only one reason for it, too hard to learn and play.Saying this, I was quiet intrigued with this game just because it looks fun. Let me tell you I was spot on. You do not have to remember how to start an engine and all the rest. All you have to do is to push up the throttle and you get to the fight within a minute and shoot planes. “RIGHT NOW AT 3 O’CLOCK!”All fighter planes from the era are well represented in this game. Graphically, this game could have been better but you can’t have everything. To be honest they are decent.For the controls side of it, I think using the mouse and keyboard is about as weird as it sounds. It will take you a little time to master both setups anyway.You can play as a single player and have 3 campaigns at your disposal (Pacific, Africa and Battle of Britain). You also have a survival, capture the flag, dogfight, team deathmatch and defend the base which can be played against the AI. Multiplayer mode is also available.Positives:~~~~~~~~-	Challenging and really fun to play-	Plenty of modes including multiplayer-	Runs smoothly-	Stack of achievements-	Trading cardsNegatives:~~~~~~~~-	Controls slightly sluggishOverall, this game is worth $9.99 and I really enjoyed it!8/10MORE THE_CPT_FROGGY REVIEWS HEREFOLLOW THE CPT FROGGY CURATOR PAGE HERE"
