76561197983740996,Recommended,304910,35365387,Posted: 30 September,all,Chane,"Sky Gamblers Storm Raiders is a simple, arcade WW2 flight simulator that's enjoyable for a couple of hours.The game covers a number of historical WW2 battles including Pearl Harbour, the battle for England etc. and the campaign brings you many of the typical locations you expect from a WW2 game, like France, Britain, Germany and the Pacific.As an Android port, graphics are not as polished as some AAA titles but the game is still fun to play.Pros:- classic dogfights- easy controls- supports joystick, keyboard and mouse- configurable controls- water looks fantastic- three different outside perspectives and cockpit view- great weather effects- option to repair your plane during fights by landing on runways (risky)- smooth gameplay, no bugs, no crashes- different weapons- huge list of WW2 air-planes, which can be unlocked throughout the course of the game- nice campaign (although a little too simple)- volumetric clouds- smooth multiplayer access, just log in and join a game any time- active multiplayer, I was always able to find mp games (although not many)- different multiplayer game modesCons:- planes all feel very similar- repetitive gameplay (but that's in the nature of dogfights)- poor textures- aircraft's do not exceed their respective maximum speed, even not when nose-diving"
