,Recommended,304910,23410284,"Posted: 5 June, 2016",all,Charismatic Stallion,"My eyes might be bad, but this game is still fun. When I was in school, one of my favorite games for the PS2 was Secret Weapons over Normandy. This game feels similar with a bit more contol, which is a good thing. There are lots of planes to unlock, ranging from early WWII fighters to jets that came in toward the end of the war. Different campaigns have you flying planes from both Allied and Axis sides. Combat is fast and fun. The music is pretty decent.If you're a person who needs every single aspect of flight rendered in perfect scientific detail, this game might not be for you, but if you're like me and you love WWII planes, this game is a great investment for only 10 USD. If you get it when it's on sale, even better!Cons to be aware of:No voice acting. All mission prompts are via text on screen. My vision sucks so I missed some.Several planes, but it feels like more could have been added. 99 cent DLCs with 5-8 planes would be nice.Music can get a bit repetitive, but you don't notice if you're fighting.I can't figure out how to lower landing gear."
