76561198188787550,Recommended,304910,15464912,"Posted: 20 April, 2015",all,Splinterfuzz,"To start with this is an arcade game and not a simulator, it was ported from phone to pc I think and they did quite a good job of it.  I personally play it with a joystick and I have to say for a phone port this game has better joystick response than War Thunder when last i played that game.  I had no trouble mapping buttons or with responsiveness in Storm Raiders compared to the buggy and mouse bias War Thunder which is a flight simulation game.  That aside I really have been enjoying this game.Pros:-Very easy to fly, it's just throttle up and you're off, this is an arcade game after all.-3 Difficulty settings.-Simple 3 modes wingman support: Attack / Defend / Formation-Multiple control types supported, works great with a flight stick. (I use the Logitech Extreme 3D Pro)-Good graphics, effects, & atmosphere music with the exception of one of the campaign missions.-Larger scale air battles with large maps, you'll get into some decent furballs here.-Three short campaigns filled with fun as well as several solo game modes that mimic the multiplayer games.-Active multiplayer online matches. (Deathmatch, Capture the Flag, & Destroy the Base.)-Unlimited bullets with a heat mechanic, recharged rockets/bombs/torpedos mechanic. (Also a con for those who want realism.)-Toggle Aim Assist, personally I found it easier with this disabled as I could kill enemies from outside the lead que range.-New aircraft are earned by completing the campaigns and leveling up, you don't have to purchase them like the phone version.Cons:-There's only one internal cockpit model used in every plane, very sad. :(-The campaigns are pretty short, about 5-6 missions long each it wont take long to finish them. (Also a pro for casuals.)-For those that like realism, there's unlimited ammo & a radar system. (Again, it's an arcade game.)-The physics are not the greatest but only really is bothersome when landing, if you cut your engine by boosting too much, or running out of fuel via campaign event. (There is no actual fuel consumption.) My first landing in this game dropped me dead from 2 meters up for a successful three point landing vtol style.  If you want a more realistic landing don't try to coast, go in low at 50% and grind the ground, wheels deploy automatically and then drop the throttle back. When you run out of fuel or kill your engine (temp only) you quite literally will start to drop straight down shortly after, there is no gliding in this game.Really there isn't a whole lot about this game that bothers me, I really like flight games like the Ace Combat series up to game 5. (Assault Horizon was just a disappointment.)  While this game isn't an Ace Combat with an amazing story I found the gameplay engaging and fun.  At $9.99 I feel the game is well worth it."
