,Recommended,304910,33407385,Posted: 9 July,all,hitsman4u,Sky Gamblers: Storm Raiders gets a definite 4/5 from me with only a couple of minor faults to complain of. In general though I have found the game entertaining and action packed with three Campaign categories which can be played at one of three levels: Rookie/Pilot or Ace. The variety of aircraft is good although all seem to share the same Messerschmitt Bf-109 cockpit and once unlocked via playing the campaigns they can be used online where the multiplayer appears to be far from dead. Features a free flight and a number of combat situation modes putting you up against AI aircraft which are marked clearly with target indicators when playing at easy levels. The only problems to report are that at times the AI aircraft and multiplayer aircraft do not manoeuver smoothly and that as you manoeuver your aircraft particularly at high speed the blackout effect kicks in annoyingly and that this cannot be disabled. I just found this frustrating during dogfight and survival missions as it blacks out all target indications as well as the screen. You literally cannot see a thing even when playing at easy levels and this could serve as an impediment to learning the game / learning the different types of aircraft and what they are capable of. Definitely worth the GBP £4.99 spent on it though.
